the people you meet one of the joys of reading fiction is in the people you meet on the way . the truly great books have you almost grieving for the characters to whom you must say goodbye as you close the book . so it is with the gold bug variations - i miss ressler too . you 'll read the prose that approaches poetry , the virtuosity , the contrapuntal style ( not contrapunctal , as one reviewer put it ) , and the breadth of subject material . all of these delight and dazzle , but with ressler , powers reaches the heart